-- HSBC Bank Sells 7.22 Million Lira of 6.75% Uridashi Notes
-- B y   H a r u m i   I c h i k u r a
-- 2012-02-20T10:01:06Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-02-20/hsbc-bank-sells-7-22-million-lira-of-6-75-uridashi-notes.html
The following uridashi bond went
on sale. Uridashi bonds are debt issued in the euromarket
and sold mainly to Japanese individual investors.  Issuer:              HSBC Bank plc
Amount:              7.22 million Turkish Lira
Coupon:              6.75 percent
Duration:            Three years
Sales period:        Feb. 17 - Feb. 24
Settlement date:     Feb. 28, 2012
Maturity:            Feb. 27, 2015
Uridashi Manager:    Aizawa Securities Co.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Harumi Ichikura in London at   hichikura@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Marco Babic at   mbabic@bloomberg.net  